Revenue-Based Software License (RBSL)
Version 1.0
Overview
This software is licensed under the Revenue-Based Software License (RBSL). This license allows you to use, modify, and distribute the software freely if your annual revenue from using it is under $100,000 USD. Above that threshold, you are required to share 10% of your revenue with the license holder.
Detailed Terms

1. Permissions
   You are permitted to:

Use the software for any purpose
Modify the software
Distribute the software
Use the software commercially, subject to revenue sharing requirements
Create and distribute derivative works

2. Revenue Sharing Requirements
   For Users Below Revenue Threshold:

If your annual revenue from using this software is less than $100,000 USD:

No payment is required
Must still comply with all other license terms

For Users Above Revenue Threshold:

If your annual revenue equals or exceeds $100,000 USD:

Must pay 10% of annual revenue to the license holder
Payments must be made quarterly
Payments are due within 30 days of quarter end
All payments must be in USD

3. Revenue Definition
   Revenue includes:

Direct sales of products using this software
Revenue from services provided using this software
Revenue from products enhanced by this software
Any other monetary benefit derived from using this software

4. Obligations
   Reporting Requirements
   You must provide quarterly reports including:

Total revenue generated using the software
Calculation of fees due
Description of how the software was used
Reports must be submitted within 30 days of quarter end

Technical Requirements
You must:

Include this license in any distribution
Mark all modified files with clear notices of changes
Maintain all copyright and attribution notices
Keep accurate records of software usage and revenue

5. Compliance and Auditing

You must maintain accurate revenue records
License holder may request reasonable audits
You must provide access to relevant records during audits

6. Disclaimers
   No Warranty
   THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE AND NONINFRINGEMENT.
   Limitation of Liability
   IN NO EVENT SHALL THE AUTHORS OR COPYRIGHT HOLDERS BE LIABLE FOR ANY CLAIM, DAMAGES OR OTHER LIABILITY, WHETHER IN AN ACTION OF CONTRACT, TORT OR OTHERWISE, ARISING FROM, OUT OF OR IN CONNECTION WITH THE SOFTWARE OR THE USE OR OTHER DEALINGS IN THE SOFTWARE.
7. Termination

License automatically terminates if you violate any terms
Upon termination, you must cease all use and distribution
Downstream users who comply with the license may retain their rights

8. Acceptance
   Using, modifying, or distributing the software indicates your acceptance of these terms.
